        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 12 at 3:19PM CDT by NWS Corpus Christi TX</headline>
        <description>At 319 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Annaville, or 7 miles north of Corpus Christi International Airport,
moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Corpus Christi, Portland, Taft, Corpus Christi International Airport,
Gregory, Del Mar College Windward Campus, Corpus Christi North Beach,
Cole Park, Del Mar College Heritage Campus, Clarkwood, Downtown
Corpus Christi, Taft Southwest, and Tuloso.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 37 between mile markers 1 and 10.
US Highway 181 between mile markers 630 and 648.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
